value.0: You have my attention. Wait, you're one of the patchwork recruits, aren't you? Ahh, you're no substitute for experience.
Not a thing. Have not heard of such a cure. My life's on the line to keep the streets clear of rioters and looters.
You good with a weapon? Shining Knight Arms and Armor has the best gear - I shop there myself. They're here in the City Core.
And if you want someone to back you up, check the Trade of Blades mercenary enclave south of here. Good people there.
You're a spell-tosser, aren't you? The Cloaktower is in the Beggar's Nest, and might have what you need.
You look... I don't know, devout, I guess. You might want to check out the Halls of Justice here in the City Core.
You need nature-related supplies, don't you? You look the type. You should visit the Druid Tree in the Docks district.
Make sure I don't catch you around the Docks. There's a sneaky merchant there. You kind of look the type...
Which do you have questions about? There's the Beggar's Nest, the Docks, the Blacklake district, and the City Core. There's also a fortified prison south of here. You need to know them all.
The City Core here holds the prison. There's a good number of staff that live in the area, as well as people on their way out.
There's not much we can do. Muggers and bands of thugs have the run of the place now especially in the sewers. I guess they won the war...
Of course, with most of what remains of the militia here, the other districts are suffering. Hopefully that's where you can help.
